The paper discusses extensions to Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that deals with logic programming. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with logic and set theory, which are topics covered in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The use of generalized atoms in ASP is a topic covered in cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the complexity of different semantics, which is a topic covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
